e shows how this principle can help unite diverse areas of biology, ranging from quantitative genetics and the theory of the levels of selection to evo-devo, ecology, physiology, and conservation biology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEvolution (Biology) 0aEvolution (Biology). 0aEvolutionary genetics. 0aIntelligent design (Teleology) 0aIntelligent design (Teleology). 0aNatural selection. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aaristotle.  abiology.  acharles darwin.  achristianity.  aconceptual framework.  aconservation biology.  adarwin.  aecology.  aevo devo.  aevolution.  aevolutionary biology.  aevolutionary explanation.  aevolutionary theory.  aexistence.  aexperiments.  agenetic drift.  agenetic load.  aintelligent design.  amaterialism.  anatural evolution.  anatural selection.  aon the origin of species.  aphysiology.  aplato.  aquantitative genetics.  arational theology.  asocrates.  astructure of the universe.  ateleology.  atheoretical.  auniverse as a watch.  awilliam paley.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094440440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944404423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944404/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles